com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface ElementEntry


  • public interface ElementEntry
    An entry for UPA ElementList that can house any DataTypes, including primitive types, set-defined types, or container types. If ElementEntry is a part of updating information and contains a primitive type, any previously stored or displayed data is replaced. If the ElementEntry contains another container type, action values associated with that type indicate how to modify data.
    See Also:
    ElementList

        void clear()
        Clears ElementEntry object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, ElementEntry object can be reused without using clear().

      • encodeInit

        int encodeInit(EncodeIterator iter,
               int encodingMaxSize)
        Encodes an ElementEntry from a complex type, such as a container type or an array. Used for aggregate elements, such as element lists. Typical use:
        1. Call encodeInit()
        2. Call one or more encoding methods for the complex type using the same buffer
        3. Call encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        encodingMaxSize - max expected encoding size of element data
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeComplete

        int encodeComplete(EncodeIterator iter,
                   boolean success)
        Completes encoding an ElementEntry for a complex type. Typical use:
        1. Call encodeInit()
        2. Call one or more encoding methods for the complex type using the same buffer
        3. Call encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        success - If true - successfully complete the aggregate, if false - remove the aggregate from the buffer.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • name

        void name(Buffer name)
        A Buffer containing the name associated with this ElementEntry. Element names are defined outside of UPA, typically as part of a domain model specification or dictionary. It Is possible for a name to be empty; however this provides no identifying information for the element.
        Parameters:
        name - the name to set

      • name

        Buffer name()
        A Buffer containing the name associated with this ElementEntry. Element names are defined outside of UPA, typically as part of a domain model specification or dictionary. It Is possible for a name to be empty; however this provides no identifying information for the element.
        Returns:
        the name

      • dataType

        void dataType(int dataType)
        Defines the DataTypes of this ElementEntry's contents. Must be in the range of DataTypes.INT - 255.
        • While encoding, set this to the enumerated value of the target type.
        • While decoding, dataType describes the type of contained data so that the correct decoder can be used. If set-defined data is used, dataType will indicate any specific DataTypes information as defined in the set definition.
        Parameters:
        dataType - the dataType to set

      • dataType

        int dataType()
        Defines the DataTypes of this ElementEntry's contents.
        • While encoding, set this to the enumerated value of the target type.
        • While decoding, dataType describes the type of contained data so that the correct decoder can be used. If set-defined data is used, dataType will indicate any specific DataTypes information as defined in the set definition.
        Returns:
        the dataType

      • encodedData

        void encodedData(Buffer encodedData)
        Encoded content in this ElementEntry. If populated on encode methods, this indicates that data is pre-encoded and encData copies while encoding.
        Parameters:
        encodedData - the encodedData to set

      • encodedData

        Buffer encodedData()
        Encoded content in this ElementEntry. While decoding, this refers to the encoded ElementEntry's payload.
